Date of Birth: September 16, 1852<br/>
Birthplace: Toms River, New Jersey, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: October 6, 1907<br/>
Death: September 23, 1934<br/>
<br/>
Born Sept. 16, 1852, at Toms River, Ocean Co., New Jersey, to Israel Joins and Anna Lowrie. Ordained apostle Oct. 6, 1907, by Joseph F. Smith, at age 55; sustained as second counselor to President Heber J. Grant March 10, 1921, at age 68; sustained as first counselor to President Grant May 28,1925; died Sept. 23, 1934, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 82.